1 概念

模型类型

  • descriptive model 描述性模型

  • 通常用于判断和展示数据的某种特征或趋势

  • inferential model 推论性模型

  • 用于解释问题或验证假设

  • 常见的假设检验都属于这类

  • predictive model 预测性模型

  • 计算预测值，确保预测值和新数据真实值之间的保真度足够高

  • 关注的是预测值本身，而非预测方法；同时关注预测的偏差

  • 特定模型可以同时属于以上三种模型类型，看你怎么用

另外一些术语

  • 监督supervised和非监督unsupervised
  • supervised models分两大类：回归regression和分类classification。

3 base R modeling

一个例子

data(crickets, package = "modeldata")
glimpse(crickets)
## Rows: 31
## Columns: 3
## $ species <fct> O. exclamationis, O. exclamationis, O. exclamationis, O. excla…
## $ temp    <dbl> 20.8, 20.8, 24.0, 24.0, 24.0, 24.0, 26.2, 26.2, 26.2, 26.2, 28…
## $ rate    <dbl> 67.9, 65.1, 77.3, 78.7, 79.4, 80.4, 85.8, 86.6, 87.5, 89.1, 98…
# help(package = "modeldata")
p <- 
  ggplot(
    crickets, 
    aes(x = temp, y = rate, color = species, shape = species, linetype = species)
  ) + 
  geom_point(size = 2) + 
  geom_smooth(method = lm, se = FALSE, alpha = 0.5) + 
  scale_color_brewer(palette = "Paired") +
  theme_bw() +
  labs(x = "Temperature (C)", y = "Chirp Rate (per minute)")
p
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

R的formula提供好多语法糖：

  • y ~ x + z + x:z可以简写成y ~ (x + z)^2或者y ~ x * z，
  • y ~ (x + z + w)^3包括了所有单因素，双因素和三因素组合
  • y ~ (.)^3 所有不在波浪号左边的变量都被包含在.里
  • y ~ I( (Celsius * 9/5) + 32 )从摄氏转华氏，用I()函数引入计算，或者其它更华丽的函数
# help(formula)

回到例子：

interaction_fit <- lm(rate ~ (temp + species)^2, data = crickets)

print(interaction_fit)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = rate ~ (temp + species)^2, data = crickets)
## 
## Coefficients:
##           (Intercept)                   temp       speciesO. niveus  
##               -11.041                  3.751                 -4.348  
## temp:speciesO. niveus  
##                -0.234

下推论之前，应该先诊断模型！

par(mfrow = c(1, 2))

# Show residuals vs predicted values:
plot(interaction_fit, which = 1)
# A normal quantile plot on the residuals:
plot(interaction_fit, which = 2)

测试一个不怎么地的模型：

# 去掉了interaction
main_effect_fit <-  lm(rate ~ temp + species, data = crickets)

anova(main_effect_fit, interaction_fit)  # 方差分析

p值为0.25，不能否定原假设（两个模型没差别），说明两个模型没差别，说明interaction影响不大。

别忘了做模型诊断：

par(mfrow = c(1, 2))
plot(main_effect_fit, which = 1)
plot(main_effect_fit, which = 2)

模型的更多统计信息：

summary(main_effect_fit)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = rate ~ temp + species, data = crickets)
## 
## Residuals:
##     Min      1Q  Median      3Q     Max 
## -3.0128 -1.1296 -0.3912  0.9650  3.7800 
## 
## Coefficients:
##                   Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)    
## (Intercept)       -7.21091    2.55094  -2.827  0.00858 ** 
## temp               3.60275    0.09729  37.032  < 2e-16 ***
## speciesO. niveus -10.06529    0.73526 -13.689 6.27e-14 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Residual standard error: 1.786 on 28 degrees of freedom
## Multiple R-squared:  0.9896, Adjusted R-squared:  0.9888 
## F-statistic:  1331 on 2 and 28 DF,  p-value: < 2.2e-16

解释：

  • 气温每变化1（摄氏度），这两个种的蟋蟀叫叫频率都上升3.6，p值显著
  • 在所有温度下，O.niveus的叫叫频率比O. exclamationis小10，同样p值显著
  • 截距：两个种的蟋蟀在0摄氏度时叫叫频率为-7.2，这个外推（extrapolation）明显不对。所以该模型只在检测的温度区间内比较合理。

如果需要预测的话，可以用predict()函数：

tb_new_value <- tibble(species = "O. exclamationis", temp = 15:20)
predict(main_effect_fit, tb_new_value)
##        1        2        3        4        5        6 
## 46.83039 50.43314 54.03589 57.63865 61.24140 64.84415

R modeling系统的问题

最大的问题就是inconsistency吧，不同作者开发的package有各自的习惯，对缺失值的处理也各不相同。

# 引入缺失值
tb_new_value$temp[1] <- NA

predict(main_effect_fit, tb_new_value)
##        1        2        3        4        5        6 
##       NA 50.43314 54.03589 57.63865 61.24140 64.84415

换一种缺失值处理方式：

predict(main_effect_fit, tb_new_value, na.action = na.fail)
## Error in na.fail.default(structure(list(temp = c(NA, 16L, 17L, 18L, 19L, : missing values in object

再换一种：

predict(main_effect_fit, tb_new_value, na.action = na.omit)
##        2        3        4        5        6 
## 50.43314 54.03589 57.63865 61.24140 64.84415

结合tidymodel和base R

tidymodels提供一系列接口，让模型结果格式符合tidyverse的设计理念：

corr_res <- purrr::map(
  .x = mtcars %>% select(-mpg),
  .f = ~ cor.test(x = .x, y = mtcars$mpg)
)

length(corr_res)  # a list of length 10
## [1] 10
corr_res[[1]]
## 
##  Pearson's product-moment correlation
## 
## data:  .x and mtcars$mpg
## t = -8.9197, df = 30, p-value = 6.113e-10
## alternative hypothesis: true correlation is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -0.9257694 -0.7163171
## sample estimates:
##       cor 
## -0.852162

用tidymodels整理上述模型：

broom::tidy(corr_res[[1]])

批量整理顺便画图：

corr_res %>% 
  purrr::map_dfr(.f = broom::tidy, .id = "predictor") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = fct_reorder(predictor, estimate))) +
  geom_point(aes(y = estimate)) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = conf.low, ymax = conf.high), width = 0.1) +
  theme_bw() +
  labs(x = NULL, y = "Correlation with `mpg`")

另一个例子：使用crickets数据，但是对不同种分开建模。

data_by_species <- 
  crickets %>% 
  group_nest(species)
glimpse(data_by_species)
## Rows: 2
## Columns: 2
## $ species <fct> O. exclamationis, O. niveus
## $ data    <list<tibble[,2]>> [<tbl_df[14 x 2]>], [<tbl_df[17 x 2]>]

这里用到了dplyr的list-column功能。

model_by_species <- 
  data_by_species %>% 
  mutate(
    model = purrr::map(data, .f = ~ lm(rate ~ temp, data = .x))
  )
model_by_species
model_by_species %>% 
  mutate(coef = purrr::map(model, .f = broom::tidy)) %>% 
  select(species, coef) %>% 
  unnest(cols = c(coef))
